From: Hybrid Token-Efficient Routing Agent
Date: 2026
Subject: Skip local model inference after runtime deadline

The runtime deadline guard (MAX_RUNTIME_SECONDS) previously only prevented
remote escalation — remaining tasks still ran a full local Gemma inference
pass (80-150s each) before the fallback logic kicked in, causing total
wall-clock runtime to exceed the 10-minute hard limit.

Fix: once deadline_hit is True, skip local_model.generate() entirely for
all remaining tasks. Cache hits and deterministic math solves still proceed
(since they cost <1ms). Everything else returns a zero-cost placeholder.

Also tighten MAX_RUNTIME_SECONDS default from 540 to 420 to leave more
safety margin for container startup and model load time.

---
 agent/task_runner.py | 33 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 28 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

